The paper proposes a method for feature selection in gene data sets using regularized random forest (RRF) and an enhanced version called guided RRF (GRRF). The paper discusses the performance of the method in terms of accuracy and computational efficiency. This work is related to machine learning (ML) and data mining, specifically in the area of feature selection. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
